column47: This is interesting. I tended to think of any personal income growth as good, even if it was low.
wasn't clear if %change was from previous year or based on original income level.
wish there was a wider variation of choices....."fairly good" covers a really wide area, for example, and could be used for a big difference in performance of the economy.
I looked at the overall trends.
For the first few questions,  I had nothing to compare the data to so I wasn't sure whether a certain amount constituted good or very good compared to the rest of the results.

The percentage weight was actually difficult to determine because there were a few times when I took all of the years into account equally to decide whether the 4th year was actually in a good standing by comparison.
I thought many of the questions were similar and hard to judge which would leave people better off.
In general, I called terms with mostly increases good and terms with mostly decreases poor.
Very interesting.  Made me think about long range economic goals vs. short range goals.
I am curious as to what the findings of this survey would be.
I enjoyed it. Thanks for the opportunity.

kinda intersting, but a bit confusing. had to really look at the side scale verses the bottom scale after reading the question. Maybe put the question at the top and leave the answers at the bottom next time to help break up the look
